<html><head><title>Interview with George Scotto at PlanetEQ</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Interview with George Scotto at PlanetEQ</h3><p>Kwill of <a href="http://www.planeteq.com/">PlanetEQ</a> recently had a chance to talk with Vice President of Customer Service and Quality Assurance, George Scotto.  Here's a clip.<br><blockquote><br><i>Kwill: What will be your hierarchy for dealing with player problems? Which problems will take precedence?</i><br><br>GS: There really is not a formal hierarchy for dealing with player problems; however we always prioritize Terms of Service violations (harassment, zone disruption, etc…), “stuck character” issues and problems directly preventing game play.<br></blockquote><br>Be sure to check it out!</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Tue 06 Jul 2004<br>Link: http://eqvault.ign.com//index.php#166<br>Printed On: Fri Nov 26 21:42:24 PST 2004<br>©2004 IGN Entertainment</font></span>